'''Yasaka Shrine''' ({{ill|Yasaka Shrine|ja|八坂神社|12=draft|12=draft}}) in Miyama is a {{ill|Shinto Shrine|ja|神社|12=draft|12=draft}} located in Sahara Honjuku of {{ill|Miyama City|ja|みやま市|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Fukuoka Prefecture|ja|福岡県|12=draft|12=draft}}. Its former ranking was that of a prefectural shrine. Its old name was “{{ill|Setaka Gion-gu|ja|瀬高祇園宮|12=draft|12=draft}}” or “{{ill|Setaka Kamishō Gion-gu|ja|瀬高上庄祇園宮|12=draft|12=draft}},” which has earned it the popular nickname “Gion-san of Miyama.”

== History ==
(Briefly similar to the Katori version, noting the relocation and local traditions.)

== Festivals and Annual Events ==
* The festival follows the same schedule as in the Katori article.

== Access ==
* Directions similar to the Katori version, adjusted for Miyama.

== Surroundings ==
* See also: {{ill|Suigyo Sahara Yamashaikan|ja|水郷佐原山車会館|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Suwa Shrine|ja|諏訪神社|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Sahara Machinami|ja|佐原の町並み|12=draft|12=draft}}, and {{ill|Katori Jingu|ja|香取神宮|12=draft|12=draft}}.

{{shinto-stub}}

